Prime exposure on bustling Scarborough Beach Road in the heart of the Osborne Park Showroom Precinct. The tenancy presents well and provides excellent signage opportunities.

Rare opportunity to join other major national retailers such as Officeworks, Freedom Furniture, Harvey Norman, JB Hi-Fi, Snooze and BBQ's Galore.

Common.PostalAddresses.Common.Line1: Cnr King Edward Rd & Howe St
Cnr King Edward Rd & Howe St

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Situated on the prominent corner of King Edward Road and Howe Street, Osborne Park this striking building offers unrivalled exposure and statement for prospective tenants.

The property comprises a 750sqm double height showroom with a 350sqm mezzanine towards the rear. A bold fascia with double height glazing ensures maximum impact on passing traffic.

King Edward road has risen in prominence as a showroom destination and is now one of the most sought after location s in WA due to its accessibility and host of big name retailers currently in residence.

Available December 2008

Osborne Park is the premier Bulky Goods precinct in WA and King Edward Road forms a primary arterial road connecting the freeway to Scarborough Beach Road. Osborne Park is situated approximately 8km north-west of Perth CBD.

Located on the golden mile in Osborne Park this prime showroom offers sensational branding opportunity in an extremely rare position on what is arguably the best large format retail precinct in WA.

Close neighbouring major national retailers include but not limited to Furniture Bazaar, Kambo's, Super Amart, and The Good Guys.

The property also offers;
• Estimated population catchment of 433,966 persons within a 10km radius
• Great signage
• Evaporative air-conditioning
• Rear access
• Ample onsite parking

This modern showroom development offers a rare opportunity in Perth's most highly sought after business locations, Osborne Park.

This corner building was purpose built to incorporate high ceilings, minimal columns, large signage panels across the faAƒÂ§ade, ample parking (including under croft), internal goods lift and attractive landscaping.

The property is situated seven (7) kilometres north west of the Perth CBD on the corner of Frobisher and Neil Street being the first ntersection from Scarbourough Beach Road as the the major arterial road for east and west bound traffic and  in close proximity to Hutton Street being a main accessway to the Mitchell Freeway.

Situated in the midst of the ever busy commerical presinct, the property offers all the value of being within the thriving Osborne Park precinct whilst having easy access and parking facilities for customers and suppliers.

A refurbished 2 level office development constructed of brick elevations with concrete footings and floor. The office areas are carpeted, painted, partitioned and airconditioned creating a modern office layout for the tenant.

There is secure undercover parking available in the complex. There is also storage area available to the tenant. Quality premises in a very accessible location.

Units 2 is approx. 310sqm of ground floor office/warehouse with a front office entrance and rear roller door access. The unit comes with 4 rear carbays and 1 undercover carbay.
